                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue required two changes, one to the dispatcher, and one to the documentation.\n\nIn the dispatcher, I now catch exceptions from action controllers. If caught, it then checks the output buffer level against that present before dispatching the action, and it closes the buffers as necessary.\n\nIn the documentation, I also added a section explaining how to clear the response body if so desired.\n\nRevisions committed in r5336.",
